06/03/2005
TIRANA, Albania -- The OSCE Presence in Tirana urged authorities on Friday (4 March) to quickly implement the new Electoral Code requirements, ensuring timely preparations for the summer parliamentary elections. A day after parliament finally passed the long-delayed law on election zones, the OSCE stressed that the government, the Central Election Commission and local authorities should immediately work to implement the new legislation and train election staff. (OSCE Web site - 04/03/05) 
